questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot service migrating to Java 21 Virtual Threads (`Executors.newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()`) is experiencing severe performance degradation and high latency under load. Thread dumps reveal many virtual threads in the `PARKED` state, while the underlying carrier threads (`ForkJoinPool-1-worker-*`) are fully blocked. You locate the following class responsible for managing shared configuration state:

java
@Service
public class ConfigurationManager {
    private final Map<String, String> cache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public synchronized String getValue(String key) {
        if (!cache.containsKey(key)) {
            String value = fetchFromRemoteDatabase(key); // IO-bound network call (~50ms)
            cache.put(key, value);
        }
        return cache.get(key);
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where database updates inside a Spring Service method annotated with `@Transactional` are occasionally lost or fail with a `LazyInitializationException`. The codebase reveals the following processing logic:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired private OrderRepository orderRepository;

    @Transactional
    public void processOrder(Long orderId) {
        Order order = orderRepository.findById(orderId)
            .orElseThrow(() -> new EntityNotFoundException());

        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            order.setStatus(OrderStatus.PROCESSED);
            orderRepository.save(order);
        });
    }
}

You are debugging an API Gateway service that aggregates data from downstream microservices. Under high traffic, the service experiences thread pool exhaustion, resulting in timeouts for all incoming API requests. The thread dump shows all threads in your custom `ExecutorService` are blocked in a `WAITING` state. You locate this coordinator method:

java
public CompletableFuture<DataPayload> aggregateData(String userId) {
    CompletableFuture<User> userFuture = CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> userService.getUser(userId), executor);
    CompletableFuture<Preferences> prefFuture = CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> prefService.getPreferences(userId), executor);

    return CompletableFuture.allOf(userFuture, prefFuture)
        .thenApply(v -> {
            User user = userFuture.join();
            Preferences pref = prefFuture.join();
            return new DataPayload(user, pref);
        });
}
